   Alzeheimers Disease and Related Disorders, A Guide For CareGivers
   DSHS 22-450(x)

     Alzheimers disease (AD) is the most common form of dementia. Often
     called a "silent epidemic," it affects four million Americans. In
     Washington State, an estimated 65,000 people have Alzheimers
     disease...

     ...It is not easy to care for a person who has a dementing illness.
     Caregivers must realize they are not super-peoplethey are human.The
     caregiver may feel sad, discouraged, frustrated, angry, or trapped.
     These are all natural feelings and they can be dealt with in a
     positive way.
     __________________________________________________________________

